post_text:
Panthers, help me welcome Mrs. Paquette to the team! She is one of our Teacher In Residence and we are so lucky to have her!!

Hi there! My name is Ms. Paquette and this will be the start of my fourth year of teaching! I moved to Kalamazoo from Southern California last fall because my husband started medical school at WMU. It has been so fun exploring a new city and state and it was my first time experiencing a real winter! I love spending time with my family and friends at the beach, hiking, skiing, boating, or BBQing. I have three sisters and over 50 cousins that made leaving California hard, but I am so excited to join Paramount and become a part of your community!

post_text:
Help us welcome Ms. Lester! She is joining the 3rd Grade Team!! Her are some words from her....

Hello fellow Panthers, my name is Ms. Lester, and I am over the moon excited to be joining Paramount this year as your new 3rd grade teacher. Paramount was my elementary school and fourth grade was one of my favorite grades. It seems so surreal coming back as an adult and being able to work with students at a school that holds so many amazing memories for me. Outside of school I am an avid reader, the Tales of Winnie the Pooh being my favorite stories of all time. I also have a dog named Banner and a kitty named Sasha, and all three of us love spending time outdoors. Whether its walking, hiking, or just hanging out at our home in Portage, you can usually find us soaking up the sun. I also am big into crafting, especially painting and DIY projects, and sometimes even bring that fun in to the classroom and have students help me out. I cannot wait until fall and to get to meet all the new faces as a Paramount Panther once again!

post_text:
Introducing Ms. Porter. Welcome to the team Ms. Porter!

"My name is Ms. Porter and I have taught special education for 7 years now, but have been in education much longer than that! I graduated from Bangor High School in 1998 and recieved my bachelor's from Western Michigan University in 2003 in secondary social studies and history. My educational experiences include teaching in South Carolina, subbing for Kalamazoo Public Schools, and working as a professional in Comstock by the time I graduated with my Master's in special education from Western Michigan University in 2011. I finally landed my first position at Lighthouse Academy in Grand Grand Rapids and served there 3 years. I have spent 4 years with my previous school, Lakeside Academy. I live in Kalamazoo and my hobbies include walking, swimming, playing video games, shopping, cooking, and collecting squirrel things. They are my favorite animal! I am also the proud mom of 2 Guinea pigs! "

post_text:
We are so excited to welcome our scholars back to school in the fall. We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment.

However, we realize that things can change between now and then. That is why we have been doing extensive planning, so we are ready to provide your child the best possible education, no matter how COVID-19 affects our community.

Besides our traditional in-person learning environment, we have detailed plans for remote and hybrid (in-person and remote) learning. Even if circumstances mean we must transition from one learning environment to another, your child will have a seamless educational experience.

We will continue to provide updates in the coming weeks as more details become available. Thank you for trusting us to educate your child!

post_text: Follow these two cute penguins as the travel Shedd Aquarium!
shared_text:
Shedd Aquarium
March 16 at 5:10 PM ·

The adventure continues! 🐧🐧
This morning, Edward and Annie explored the rotunda. They are a bonded pair of rockhopper penguins, which means they are together for nesting season. Every spring is nesting season for the penguins here at Shedd, and this year is no different! Next week, penguins, including Edward and Annie, will begin to build their nests. You’re invited to digitally join us for the nesting coverage!

In the meantime, we will share a variety of animal activities, and yes, Wellington will return! While this may be a strange time for us, these days are relatively normal for the penguins and other animals at Shedd. Our caregivers are constantly providing new activities, experiences, food and more to allow the animals to express natural behaviors—even if that includes simply exploring. Let us know what penguin activities you want to see! 👇

‪On Monday, March 16th-Wednesday, March 18th, the PCA office will be open from 9am-3pm. During this time, please feel free to stop by to pick up any medication (inhalers, epi-pens, etc) we may be storing in the office for your child that you would like to have at home over this extended time frame. Also, if your child left any items in their classroom they want or an item or two that was lost in the LOST and FOUND, this would be a great time to pick it up.‬
‪ ‬
‪During this time away from school, continue to keep your child reading, practicing math facts, completing student learning packets, playing board games, doing chores, and going outside for some fresh air and physical activity. These activities are good for the whole family. Keeping a routine and limiting screen time is also good while on this extended time away from school. ‬
‪ ‬
‪I will continue to to stay in touch. If you have any questions, feel free to contact me. I will miss all my PCA students and families, but know that we will be back together soon!‬

‪All In, ‬
‪Ms. Welc‬

Dear Paramount Families, we invite you to set up an E-Wallet online for your student(s). This will allow a set amount that your child can spend. Any unused money in the E-Wallet will be returned to the parent. You can also add to classroom library!

The Book Fair will be the week of conferences and OPEN both nights on the 13th and 14th from 4:00-8:00pm to shop!! This is a great fundraising opportunity for Paramount! Thank you!

post_text:
Safety Poster Contest during School Safety Week:
1. Create a poster on safety for bus, fire, tornado, playground, internet, or lock down safety
2. The rest is up to your imagination.
3. The objective of the Safety Poster Contest is to build awareness for our safety topics.
4. Students are asked to submit their FINAL poster on Thursday, October 24th to their homeroom teacher.
5. Poster is to be created by students and completed at home.
6. Poster should be 11x17 or poster board.

We will have a 1st, 2nd, 3rd place and 5 runner ups in each wing (Y5-2nd, 3rd-5th, 6th-8th). We will have some cool safety swag for students and staff who (1st, 2nd, 3rd place for staff in each wing)!
